.TH "scsi_host_alloc" 9 "scsi_host_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_host_alloc \- register a scsi host adapter instance.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct Scsi_Host *" scsi_host_alloc
.BI "(struct scsi_host_template *sht "  ","
.BI "int privsize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sht" 12
pointer to scsi host template
.IP "privsize" 12
extra bytes to allocate for driver
.SH "NOTE"
Allocate a new Scsi_Host and perform basic initialization.
The host is not published to the scsi midlayer until scsi_add_host
is called.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return value:
Pointer to a new Scsi_Host
